Business Brief -- Melville Corp.:
   Sales Are Revised Upward,
   Reflect October Acquisition
Restated sales for 1991, ended Dec. 31, increased 14% from
1990 to $9.8 billion, the company said. Same store sales rose
0.4%. The restatement includes sales from K&K Toys, which the
company acquired in October 1991. Before the K&K results were
added, sales increased 4.6% and 6.1%, respectively, for the
four week and full year periods, Melville said.
   Melville operates more than 8,000 specialty retail stores
across the U.S. and is based in Rye, N.Y.